Package com.bansheeproject

This package contains the most used classes.

          Description

Class Summary
AddressServiceData It is used to perform an invocation through the address without caring about the invocation protocol.
ExceptionResponse It is the type of response that is returned when an exception has been thrown by the service and the invocation is configured to capture a given type of exception.
HttpHeader Represents a HTTP header.
HTTPServiceData Service data type for HTTP invocations.
Response Represents the response of any service invocation.
SOAP11InvocationData Represents an implementation of service invocation using SOAP 1.1.
SOAP12InvocationData Represents an implementation of service invocation using SOAP 1.2
SOAPInvocationData Represents an implementation of service invocation using SOAP
WebServicesInvocationData It is an abstraction of a service invocation.
WSDLServiceData It represents service data provided by a WSDL.
 

Enum Summary
